You are given the following Python implementation of the Bellman-Ford algorithm intended to find shortest paths from a single source in a weighted directed graph, which may contain negative edge weights. The graph is represented as a dictionary of dictionaries where `graph[u][v]` gives the weight of edge `u -> v`.

Identify ALL bugs in this code. Your answer must:
